# Vendored third-party assets.
#
# Each row pins a file in this directory to a specific upstream
# release plus a sha256 of the bytes that release ships. The
# checksum is what `rake vendor:verify` re-computes and fails
# on mismatch — a CI break here means "the vendored file on
# disk no longer matches what we said it does", which is the
# signal we want.
#
# Bumping a vendored dependency:
#   1. Download the new release from upstream + at least one
#      mirror (CDN or GitHub release asset).
#   2. Cross-check sha256 across sources before trusting the
#      bytes.
#   3. Update this file (filename, version, source URL, sha256).
#   4. Open a manual PR — Dependabot is configured to ignore
#      this directory.
#
# Format: sha256 (64 hex chars)  two spaces  filename
# Lines starting with `#` and blank lines are ignored.
